<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Brazil</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-11-16"><hi rend="italic">November 16,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I thank you cordially for the kind words sent to me on behalf of
                            President Roosevelt, now traveling in the South. You are well acquainted
                            with the friendly feelings of the Government and people of Brazil toward
                            the United States of America.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Affonso Penna</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>